places.name: Narikala Fortress
places.description: An ancient fortress overlooking Tbilisi, offering stunning views of the city and a glimpse into its historical architecture.

places.name: Old Tbilisi
places.description: A charming area filled with narrow streets, colorful balconies, and historic buildings that showcase the city's diverse culture.

places.name: Rustaveli Avenue
places.description: The main thoroughfare of Tbilisi lined with shops, theaters, and cafés, perfect for a leisurely stroll or a day of sightseeing.

places.description: Famous for their therapeutic properties, these traditional baths are a unique experience in the heart of the city.

places.description: A lively amusement park located on a mountain overlooking Tbilisi, with fun rides and panoramic views of the city.

places.name: Fabrika
places.description: A trendy spot that combines a hostel, bar, and café, attracting locals and tourists alike for its vibrant atmosphere.

places.name: Georgian National Museum
places.description: A comprehensive museum showcasing the rich history and culture of Georgia through various exhibits.

places.name: Freedom Square
places.description: A central plaza in Tbilisi that is a hub for social and political gatherings, surrounded by significant buildings and landmarks.

places.name: Chronicle of Georgia
places.description: A monumental sculpture that tells the story of Georgia's history, located on a hill with spectacular city views.
